<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-03-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-03-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="1355" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1355">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The</hi>
                            <gloss type="from">
                                <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State</hi>
                            </gloss>
                            <hi rend="italic">to the Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MH1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Morgenthau</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-03-02">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 2, 1915</hi>.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>446. Your 459, February 28, does not clearly indicate what message German
                            Ambassador desires you to communicate to commander Allied fleet, but it
                            would appear that message you are requested to <pb facs="1220" n="962" xml:id="pg_962"/> communicate might more properly be given by
                            Turkish military commander. If, however, it is proposed to evacuate
                            Constantinople, you may, if requested, act as intermediary to save city
                            from bombardment.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_BWJ1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>